}
</style>
<small>shape: (2, 2)</small><table border="1" class="dataframe"><thead><tr><th>Var1</th><th>Var2</th></tr><tr><td>i64</td><td>i64</td></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>2</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>4</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
```
:::
:::


### Data types

To specify data types different from the default, you also use the schema parameter:

::: {#a103854c .cell execution_count=9}
``` {.python .cell-code}
df6 = pl.DataFrame(
    {
        "Rain": [2.1, 0.5, 0.0, 1.8],
        "Cloud cover": [1, 1, 0, 2],
    },
    schema={"Rain": pl.Float32, "Cloud cover": pl.Int32}
)

df6
```

